the-css.escape()-method.name: escape
the-css.escape()-method.summary: The CSS.escape() static method returns a string containing the escaped string passed as parameter, mostly for use as part of a CSS selector.
the-css.escape()-method.title: CSS.escape()

namespacedef-css.name: CSS
namespacedef-css.summary: The CSS interface holds useful CSS-related methods. No objects with this interface are implemented: it contains only static methods and is therefore a utilitarian interface.
namespacedef-css.title: CSS

dom-cssgroupingrule-cssrules.name: cssRules
dom-cssgroupingrule-cssrules.summary: The cssRules property of the CSSGroupingRule interface returns a CSSRuleList containing a collection of CSSRule objects.
dom-cssgroupingrule-cssrules.title: CSSGroupingRule.cssRules

dom-cssgroupingrule-deleterule.name: deleteRule
dom-cssgroupingrule-deleterule.summary: The deleteRule() method of the CSSGroupingRule interface removes a CSS rule from a list of child CSS rules.
dom-cssgroupingrule-deleterule.title: CSSGroupingRule.deleteRule()

dom-cssgroupingrule-insertrule.name: insertRule
dom-cssgroupingrule-insertrule.summary: The insertRule() method of the CSSGroupingRule interface adds a new CSS rule to a list of CSS rules.
dom-cssgroupingrule-insertrule.title: CSSGroupingRule.insertRule()

the-cssgroupingrule-interface.name: CSSGroupingRule
the-cssgroupingrule-interface.summary: The CSSGroupingRule interface of the CSS Object Model represents any CSS at-rule that contains other rules nested within it.
the-cssgroupingrule-interface.title: CSSGroupingRule

dom-cssimportrule-href.name: href
dom-cssimportrule-href.summary: The read-only href property of the CSSImportRule interface returns the URL specified by the @import at-rule.
dom-cssimportrule-href.title: CSSImportRule.href

dom-cssimportrule-media.name: media
dom-cssimportrule-media.summary: The read-only media property of the CSSImportRule interface returns a MediaList object, containing the value of the media attribute of the associated stylesheet.
dom-cssimportrule-media.title: CSSImportRule.media

dom-cssimportrule-stylesheet.name: styleSheet
dom-cssimportrule-stylesheet.summary: The read-only styleSheet property of the CSSImportRule interface returns the CSS Stylesheet specified by the @import at-rule. This will be in the form of a CSSStyleSheet object.
dom-cssimportrule-stylesheet.title: CSSImportRule.stylesheet

the-cssimportrule-interface.name: CSSImportRule
the-cssimportrule-interface.summary: The CSSImportRule interface represents an @import at-rule.
the-cssimportrule-interface.title: CSSImportRule

dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.name: namespaceURI
dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.summary: The read-only namespaceURI property of the CSSNamespaceRule returns a string containing the text of the URI of the given namespace.
dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.title: CSSNamespaceRule.namespaceURI

dom-cssnamespacerule-prefix.name: prefix
dom-cssnamespacerule-prefix.summary: The read-only prefix property of the CSSNamespaceRule returns a string with the name of the prefix associated to this namespace. If there is no such prefix, it returns an empty string.
dom-cssnamespacerule-prefix.title: CSSNamespaceRule.prefix

the-cssnamespacerule-interface.name: CSSNamespaceRule
the-cssnamespacerule-interface.summary: The CSSNamespaceRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS @namespace at-rule.
the-cssnamespacerule-interface.title: CSSNamespaceRule

dom-cssgroupingrule-selectortext.name: selectorText
dom-cssgroupingrule-selectortext.summary: The selectorText property of the CSSPageRule interface gets and sets the selectors associated with the CSSPageRule.
dom-cssgroupingrule-selectortext.title: CSSPageRule.selectorText

dom-cssgroupingrule-style.name: style
dom-cssgroupingrule-style.summary: The style read-only property of the CSSPageRule interface returns a CSSStyleDeclaration object. This represents an object that is a CSS declaration block, and exposes style information and various style-related methods and properties.
dom-cssgroupingrule-style.title: CSSPageRule.style

the-csspagerule-interface.name: CSSPageRule
the-csspagerule-interface.summary: CSSPageRule represents a single CSS @page rule.
the-csspagerule-interface.title: CSSPageRule

dom-cssrule-csstext.name: cssText
dom-cssrule-csstext.summary: The cssText property of the CSSRule interface returns the actual text of a CSSStyleSheet style-rule.

ie.notes: The property normalizes rules and does not return the original verbatim rule text. For example, border-width: 1px; border-style:solid; border-color:white; returns border: 1px solid white;.

dom-cssrule-csstext.title: CSSRule.cssText

dom-cssrule-parentrule.name: parentRule
dom-cssrule-parentrule.summary: The parentRule property of the CSSRule interface returns the containing rule of the current rule if this exists, or otherwise returns null.
dom-cssrule-parentrule.title: CSSRule.parentRule

dom-cssrule-parentstylesheet.name: parentStyleSheet
dom-cssrule-parentstylesheet.summary: The parentStyleSheet property of the CSSRule interface returns the StyleSheet object in which the current rule is defined.
dom-cssrule-parentstylesheet.title: CSSRule.parentStyleSheet

the-cssrule-interface.name: CSSRule
the-cssrule-interface.summary: The CSSRule interface represents a single CSS rule. There are several types of rules which inherit properties from CSSRule.
the-cssrule-interface.title: CSSRule

dom-cssrulelist-item.name: item
dom-cssrulelist-item.summary: The item() method of the CSSRuleList interface returns the CSSRule object at the specified index or null if the specified index doesn't exist.
dom-cssrulelist-item.title: CSSRuleList.item()

dom-cssrulelist-length.name: length
dom-cssrulelist-length.summary: The length property of the CSSRuleList interface returns the number of CSSRule objects in the list.
dom-cssrulelist-length.title: CSSRuleList.length

the-cssrulelist-interface.name: CSSRuleList
the-cssrulelist-interface.summary: A CSSRuleList represents an ordered collection of read-only CSSRule objects.
the-cssrulelist-interface.title: CSSRuleList

dom-cssstyledeclaration-cssfloat.name: cssFloat
dom-cssstyledeclaration-cssfloat.summary: The cssFloat property of the CSSStyleDeclaration interface returns the result of invoking CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyValue() with float as an argument.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-cssfloat.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.cssFloat

dom-cssstyledeclaration-csstext.name: cssText
dom-cssstyledeclaration-csstext.summary: The cssText property of the CSSStyleDeclaration interface returns or sets the text of the element's inline style declaration only.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-csstext.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.cssText

dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyprior.name: getPropertyPriority
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyprior.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyPriority() method interface returns a string that provides all explicitly set priorities on the CSS property.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyprior.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyPriority()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyvalue.name: getPropertyValue
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyvalue.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyValue() method interface returns a string containing the value of a specified CSS property.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyvalue.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyValue()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-item.name: item
dom-cssstyledeclaration-item.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.item() method interface returns a CSS property name from a CSSStyleDeclaration by index.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-item.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.item()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-length.name: length
dom-cssstyledeclaration-length.summary: The read-only property returns an integer that represents the number of style declarations in this CSS declaration block.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-length.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.length

dom-cssstyledeclaration-parentrule.name: parentRule
dom-cssstyledeclaration-parentrule.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.parentRule read-only property returns a CSSRule that is the parent of this style block, e.g. a CSSStyleRule representing the style for a CSS selector.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-parentrule.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.parentRule

dom-cssstyledeclaration-removeproperty.name: removeProperty
dom-cssstyledeclaration-removeproperty.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.removeProperty() method interface removes a property from a CSS style declaration object.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-removeproperty.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.removeProperty()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-setproperty.name: setProperty
dom-cssstyledeclaration-setproperty.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.setProperty() method interface sets a new value for a property on a CSS style declaration object.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-setproperty.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.setProperty()

the-cssstyledeclaration-interface.name: CSSStyleDeclaration
the-cssstyledeclaration-interface.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration interface represents an object that is a CSS declaration block, and exposes style information and various style-related methods and properties.
the-cssstyledeclaration-interface.title: CSSStyleDeclaration

dom-cssstylerule-selectortext.name: selectorText
dom-cssstylerule-selectortext.summary: The selectorText property of the CSSStyleRule interface gets and sets the selectors associated with the CSSStyleRule.
dom-cssstylerule-selectortext.title: CSSStyleRule.selectorText

dom-cssstylerule-style.name: style
dom-cssstylerule-style.summary: The read-only style property is the CSSStyleDeclaration interface for the declaration block of the CSSStyleRule.
dom-cssstylerule-style.title: CSSStyleRule.style

the-cssstylerule-interface.name: CSSStyleRule
the-cssstylerule-interface.summary: The CSSStyleRule interface represents a single CSS style rule.
the-cssstylerule-interface.title: CSSStyleRule

dom-cssstylesheet-cssstylesheet.name: CSSStyleSheet
dom-cssstylesheet-cssstylesheet.summary: The CSSStyleSheet() constructor creates a new CSSStyleSheet object which represents a single Stylesheet.
dom-cssstylesheet-cssstylesheet.title: CSSStyleSheet()

dom-cssstylesheet-cssrules.name: cssRules
dom-cssstylesheet-cssrules.summary: The read-only CSSStyleSheet property cssRules returns a live CSSRuleList which provides a real-time, up-to-date list of every CSS rule which comprises the stylesheet. Each item in the list is a CSSRule defining a single rule.
dom-cssstylesheet-cssrules.title: CSSStyleSheet.cssRules

dom-cssstylesheet-deleterule.name: deleteRule
dom-cssstylesheet-deleterule.summary: The CSSStyleSheet method deleteRule() removes a rule from the stylesheet object.
dom-cssstylesheet-deleterule.title: CSSStyleSheet.deleteRule()

dom-cssstylesheet-insertrule.name: insertRule
dom-cssstylesheet-insertrule.summary: The CSSStyleSheet.insertRule() method inserts a new CSS rule into the current style sheet.
dom-cssstylesheet-insertrule.title: CSSStyleSheet.insertRule()

dom-cssstylesheet-ownerrule.name: ownerRule
dom-cssstylesheet-ownerrule.summary: The read-only CSSStyleSheet property ownerRule returns the CSSImportRule corresponding to the @import at-rule which imported the stylesheet into the document. If the stylesheet wasn't imported into the document using @import, the returned value is null.
dom-cssstylesheet-ownerrule.title: CSSStyleSheet.ownerRule

dom-cssstylesheet-replace.name: replace
dom-cssstylesheet-replace.summary: The replace() method of the CSSStyleSheet interface asynchronously replaces the content of the stylesheet with the content passed into it. The method returns a promise that resolves with the CSSStyleSheet object.
dom-cssstylesheet-replace.title: CSSStyleSheet.replace()

dom-cssstylesheet-replacesync.name: replaceSync
dom-cssstylesheet-replacesync.summary: The replaceSync() method of the CSSStyleSheet interface synchronously replaces the content of the stylesheet with the content passed into it.
dom-cssstylesheet-replacesync.title: CSSStyleSheet.replaceSync()

the-cssstylesheet-interface.name: CSSStyleSheet
the-cssstylesheet-interface.summary: The CSSStyleSheet interface represents a single CSS stylesheet, and lets you inspect and modify the list of rules contained in the stylesheet. It inherits properties and methods from its parent, StyleSheet.
the-cssstylesheet-interface.title: CSSStyleSheet

dom-documentorshadowroot-adoptedstyleshe.name: adoptedStyleSheets
dom-documentorshadowroot-adoptedstyleshe.summary: The adoptedStyleSheets property of the Document interface is used for setting an array of constructed stylesheets to be used by the document.
dom-documentorshadowroot-adoptedstyleshe.title: Document.adoptedStyleSheets

dom-documentorshadowroot-adoptedstyleshe.name: adoptedStyleSheets
dom-documentorshadowroot-adoptedstyleshe.summary: The adoptedStyleSheets property of the ShadowRoot interface sets an array of constructed stylesheets to be used by the shadow DOM subtree.
dom-documentorshadowroot-adoptedstyleshe.title: ShadowRoot.adoptedStyleSheets

dom-documentorshadowroot-stylesheets.name: styleSheets
dom-documentorshadowroot-stylesheets.summary: The styleSheets read-only property of the Document interface returns a StyleSheetList of CSSStyleSheet objects, for stylesheets explicitly linked into or embedded in a document.
dom-documentorshadowroot-stylesheets.title: Document.styleSheets

dom-documentorshadowroot-stylesheets.name: styleSheets
dom-documentorshadowroot-stylesheets.summary: The styleSheets read-only property of the ShadowRoot interface returns a StyleSheetList of CSSStyleSheet objects, for stylesheets explicitly linked into or embedded in a shadow tree.
dom-documentorshadowroot-stylesheets.title: ShadowRoot.styleSheets

dom-elementcssinlinestyle-style.name: style
dom-elementcssinlinestyle-style.summary: The style read-only property returns the inline style of an element in the form of a CSSStyleDeclaration object that contains a list of all styles properties for that element with values assigned for the attributes that are defined in the element's inline style attribute.
dom-elementcssinlinestyle-style.title: HTMLElement.style

dom-medialist-mediatext.name: mediaText
dom-medialist-mediatext.summary: The mediaText property of the MediaList interface is a stringifier that returns a string representing the MediaList as text, and also allows you to set a new MediaList.
dom-medialist-mediatext.title: MediaList.mediaText

the-medialist-interface.name: MediaList
the-medialist-interface.summary: The MediaList interface represents the media queries of a stylesheet, e.g. those set using a <link> element's media attribute.
the-medialist-interface.title: MediaList

dom-linkstyle-sheet.name: sheet
dom-linkstyle-sheet.summary: The read-only sheet property of the ProcessingInstruction interface represent the name of the stylesheet associated to the ProcessingInstruction.
dom-linkstyle-sheet.title: ProcessingInstruction.sheet

dom-linkstyle-sheet.name: sheet
dom-linkstyle-sheet.summary: The SVGStyleElement.sheet read-only property returns the CSSStyleSheet corresponding to the given SVG style element, or null if there is none.
dom-linkstyle-sheet.title: SVGStyleElement.sheet

dom-stylesheet-disabled.name: disabled
dom-stylesheet-disabled.summary: The disabled property of the StyleSheet interface determines whether the style sheet is prevented from applying to the document.
dom-stylesheet-disabled.title: StyleSheet.disabled

dom-stylesheet-href.name: href
dom-stylesheet-href.summary: The href property of the StyleSheet interface returns the location of the style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-href.title: StyleSheet.href

dom-stylesheet-media.name: media
dom-stylesheet-media.summary: The media property of the StyleSheet interface specifies the intended destination media for style information. It is a read-only, array-like MediaList object and can be removed with deleteMedium() and added with appendMedium().
dom-stylesheet-media.title: StyleSheet.media

dom-stylesheet-ownernode.name: ownerNode
dom-stylesheet-ownernode.summary: The ownerNode property of the StyleSheet interface returns the node that associates this style sheet with the document.
dom-stylesheet-ownernode.title: StyleSheet.ownerNode

dom-stylesheet-parentstylesheet.name: parentStyleSheet
dom-stylesheet-parentstylesheet.summary: The parentStyleSheet property of the StyleSheet interface returns the style sheet, if any, that is including the given style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-parentstylesheet.title: StyleSheet.parentStyleSheet

dom-stylesheet-title.name: title
dom-stylesheet-title.summary: The title property of the StyleSheet interface returns the advisory title of the current style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-title.title: StyleSheet.title

dom-stylesheet-type.name: type
dom-stylesheet-type.summary: The type property of the StyleSheet interface specifies the style sheet language for the given style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-type.title: StyleSheet.type

the-stylesheet-interface.name: StyleSheet
the-stylesheet-interface.summary: An object implementing the StyleSheet interface represents a single style sheet. CSS style sheets will further implement the more specialized CSSStyleSheet interface.
the-stylesheet-interface.title: StyleSheet

dom-stylesheetlist-item.name: item
dom-stylesheetlist-item.summary: The item() method of the StyleSheetList interface returns a single CSSStyleSheet object.
dom-stylesheetlist-item.title: StyleSheetList.item()

dom-stylesheetlist-length.name: length
dom-stylesheetlist-length.summary: The length read-only property of the StyleSheetList interface returns the number of CSSStyleSheet objects in the collection.
dom-stylesheetlist-length.title: StyleSheetList.length

the-stylesheetlist-interface.name: StyleSheetList
the-stylesheetlist-interface.summary: The StyleSheetList interface represents a list of CSSStyleSheet objects. An instance of this object can be returned by Document.styleSheets.
the-stylesheetlist-interface.title: StyleSheetList

dom-window-getcomputedstyle.name: getComputedStyle
dom-window-getcomputedstyle.summary: The Window.getComputedStyle() method returns an object containing the values of all CSS properties of an element, after applying active stylesheets and resolving any basic computation those values may contain.

firefox.notes: Before version 62 this function returned null when called on a Window with no presentation (e.g. an iframe with display: none; set). Since 62 it returns a CSSStyleDeclaration object with length 0, containing empty strings (bug 1467722; also see bug 1471231 for further work).

dom-window-getcomputedstyle.title: Window.getComputedStyle()

css-style-sheet-collections.name: alternate_stylesheet
css-style-sheet-collections.summary: Specifying alternative style sheets in a web page provides a way for users to see multiple versions of a page, based on their needs or preferences.
css-style-sheet-collections.title: Alternative style sheets
